cs.PL, cs.OS, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.AR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category as it presents a new concurrent language design. It may also belong to the Operating Systems (cs.OS) category as it deals with low-level memory management and locking. Additionally, it may be relevant to the Data Structures (cs.DS) category as it discusses region-based memory management. The paper also touches on software engineering (cs.SE) concepts such as ownership transfer and early deallocation. Finally, it may be relevant to the Architecture (cs.AR) category as it discusses the design of a concurrent language.
